MY HOUSE is so friggen cold. Actually, my house isn't really that cold. Every room in my house is at least a little warm, and my  room is freezing. I love it though, strangely enough. What sucks, is that today, is a hardcore studying day. I have 2 big tests tomorrow....and they're also quite hard. WOO. Just great.
School got out at like 11 today. It was totally unexpected...the power went out, and the people at school were just like...no school. And I was like...yes. Today's my day. But boy, was I wrong. I stayed at school until like 4, all by myself, but it was alot of fun. I played on the school's drumset. I played that thing so hard, I almost puked. That's how brutal I am. Oh, and I broke a drum stick. What fun.
I feel really weird right now. I want christmas break to come. Like right now. I still have finals to worry about....that's killing me right now. I can't even relax. Because here and there...I'm getting pressured to do this or that. And.....freaking teachers at our school. Well. All of my teachers are great, except for one. The teacher totally like favors these certain people in my class, and helps them do things, and encourages them, etc. It's almost like the teacher is a student, acting like she is too good for some of us. I hate her. Actually not really hate, that's too strong of a word. I'll just say I dislike her....alot. If she would just open her eyes and see what she is doing...asdk.jhldkf.
That's not the only reason I'm feeling weird. It's just...life in general. It's about how depressing life is sometimes. I'm not depressed. Not sad. Just sometimes, very lost, and confused. It seems like I'm never going to get this over with. High school. But what sucks...is that it's only going to get worse. And in college, I'm going to wish I was in high school again. And when I'm done with school....I'm going to wish I was back in college again. See, it's stuff like this that makes me so discouraged. It's almost like I'm doing this for nothing. But it's always going to be important. Whether I like it or not.
OKAY. Well i'm done ranting about school. It sucks, I guess you can say.
I'm going to fail those 2 tests tomorrow......ua,djklfhlaksjdfhs

I am selling my Ipod shuffle. Let me know if you want to buy it. 1 GB. Comes with everything that the box came with. Works perfectly. may not look like it works good....but it works just fine. comes with an extra case, and a lanyard and stuff. everything. even has the music still on it. if you have any more questions ask me.

Well.....It's been quite a while since I last posted anything. So, I shall fill you in on what's been going on lately. School. School School SCHOOL. Biology class. Sucks so hard. It's the worst class this year. I'm just happy it's the only subject this year that we don't have a final in. That would be brutal. Well, pretty much I hate every class I have at school. But whatever. School's always gonna be a bitch.
Been playing a couple shows here and there, and they've all been alright I guess. I turned 15. I got an Ipod mini. I got new CDs from mewithoutyou, rilo kiley, and death cab for cutie. I'm going to get a new icon for my eljay soon.
Life is amazing. Hard, but amazing. I have a big test to study for tomorrow, and I studied as much as I could understand, but I'm going to go study again in a couple of minutes. I guess school is the thing that takes up most of my life, even though I hate it. I need to manage my time better. I'm really happy that christmas break is next month though. October went by really fast. unbelieveable.
I don't know what's wrong with me. I'm not talking to people as much as I used to. I'm not getting much sleep. I feel like I'm sheltering myself. I don't want to. Maybe I'm too self-centered. Because all I'm saying is I. I I I I I I I. What the hell's wrong with me?
Seriously people, don't judge me for how I act. Yeah, I play in a band that sings the song "Everyday, praising Jesus Christ in every way". But no one's perfect. I'm not saying I sin on purpose. I'm showing you  that I am NOT perfect. Don't have a perfect image of me. I do many things that I regret and wish I didn't do. I don't like it. But I still have enough confidence, strength, and faith to carry on a strong relationship with God. Don't judge me.
Maybe I just need to relax. I always wish I was like some other person. I think I have self-esteem issues. I'm still a 15 year old kid who's desperate for attention, whether I like it or not. Because I, for one, think that crying out for attention is one of the stupidest moves that anyone can ever make, and I laugh at anyone who tries to pull it off. So I laugh at myself. It's a phase. I'll be okay.
I'm not making any sense right now. I really need to relax.

ALMOST THE END OF THE WEEK OMGZZZZZZZZZ

Yes. YES. I have had an okay week I guess. Everyone was in a good mood this week. I've been alot more tired than usual...which is strange, but it's okay. I've been sleeping well. I haven't been in a bad mood alot lately....so I guess that's a good thing.
OHHHHH shoot, there's one thing that is killing me right now though. PSAT's. The letter "P" will just make you say, "What's the big deal? It's just practice". I wish I could say the same. I've been stressing about this stuff alot lately, and everyone else is just like..."Eh..no big deal". I wonder why I feel so different about this. I wonder.....
I guess I'm just waaaaaaaaaaaaaay too paranoid. I want to go to a good college...and I want to live a good future. But the real SAT test is next year. Hm. Something is wrong here. If you get a good grade on PSAT.....you can get a scholarship. I guess it's the word "Scholarship" that gets me. I don't come from a rich family. School = expensive. So yeah.
OKAY I'm so fking done talking about SAT or PSAT or whatever. BLAH. I shouldn't stress about it too much.

The concert on sunday....a few days ago. It was great I guess. Number One Gun was good. They only played one old song, but the new ones were good. Mourning September was good. Spoken and Project 86 were better than I thought they would be. But yeah. It was an interesting concert.

Weekend. Time to relaxxxxxxxxxxxxxx. Joy. I could really use it.

Number one gun tomorrow. It better be a good show. Oh yeah, Mikey and Eddy are over here. Eddy leaves tomorrow morning, and me, Isaac, and Mikey get picked up to go to Greg's place, get picked up by Jackson there, and go to show. My parents are not home. hooray. and THEN! School on monday. Sleep over at Greg's tomorrow night too. I still have alot of homework to do. I hate myself. Props to Marta Wesselhoff....Because she is so cool. (I hope life will get better sweetie =]]]) She is the only person talking to me right now..But it's okay, because she's cool. (Hope I didn't scare you Marta)
Time to go. Later everyone

Time for another post. It's been a few days.
Hm. I really don't know what to say. Ohhh. Show last night. It was a good show, our friends in 3CW came out, and so did Tim. Oh, Joe's wife too. It was a fun show to play, even though there were only like 4 people there. No problem.

My amp is still in the shop. I need it back...like...now. Or else I'm going to be screwed. I've played about 4 or 5 shows without my amp, and like 5 practices without it. They said it would take 7-10 days to fix. I took my amp there like at the beginning of last month. Wtf. White people....geez.
On the way back home last night...in Sean's car...(he was driving, it was a little scary), I was soooooooooooo effing hyper. I have never been so hyper in my life. And all I ate was 2 gummy worms and half a cup of coke. I laughed at everything. Mikey told the best joke ever, and I almost died.

So yeah. That's pretty much all that happened this week. Homecoming tonight. I'm not going to the banquet though. Too expensive. 20 frikkin dollars to sit down and eat. Whoop-de-do. I'm going to the afterparty, which costs only 5. Yesssssssssssssss. I get to see Lyndsey tonight. I'm happy.

Short post. I'm at school. It's been a hell of a day. I was really hyper this morning, now I'm effing tired. I want bed. I'm stuck here until 5:30 or so. Blah. I'm so tired. I want to die. I will post later today at home.

I AM NO LONGER A VEGETARIAN.

shiiiiiiiet. I went without eating meat for about 4 months. I knew that I couldn't do it. It's okay though, I'm still straight edge. OHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH frick I got a new guitar. I am so spoiled. GOD i hate myself. SO much. I wish I wasn't such a fckin whiner. blah. I went to church today...It was fun I guess. There's always someone who's just...pissed off though...weird.

When I get my amp back.....I am all set. I have all the equipment I will need for a while. A nice guitar, a nice amp....blah blah blah FCKING spoiled.  Me and mikey started an acoustic project. We don't have a name yet...Nor do we have any songs. We are going to start ASAP. (my heaviest influence right now is i can make a mess....oh boy) SCHOOL. I love it. It's so much fun. Actually not really. I really don't like my school. They don't give a rat's ass about people who smoke and drink around and about our school...but they like go crazy on people who are wearing jewelry. My school sucks. Well, in general, pretty much about everyone that goes to a school, hates it for some reason. That's mainly my reason. And also the fact that some people at my school suck ass. I hate them all. I hate them I hate them I hate them.

I hate myspace. So much. I don't want to delete it though. To be honest. People suck. Sometimes, I just want to be alone. With someone. (I don't mean it that way). Sometimes, I'm just in this mood to be with this one special person. No one specific, I just picture it in my head. I'm sick of all these middle school crisis/relationships. "Omg, she doesn't like me, I'm gonna go kill myself."  "I want her so bad, I'd die for her". BOO HOO. Cry me a fcking river. Grow up a little and live for something else. You'll have much more to worry about than the opposite sex when you're older.

If I offended you...let me know.

I might be going over to mikey's place to sleep over. Show tomorrow. In the afternoon. Hopefully it'll go well.

What a week...month...or however long it's been since i last posted..I don't remember. Friday....played a show with the O.C. Supertones. Saturday...show at Annie's and Linda's Coffee House Extraordinaire with Three Cord Wonder. hahaha. Today...played a show with Three Cord Wonder again. It was an okay show. Sounded good. That's about it.

School is sucking really hard. Well, it's not too bad. I don't like it very much. Very busy. Homework...then soccer practice, and then band practice. I am soooooooooo busy. Sucks hardcore. There's a sale going on at guitar center tomorrow....I need a new guitar so bad. You have no idea. sjkdhalsekjghalek. I can't believe I broke my SG. Yup...still haven't gotten over it. If you're thinking "He's such a girl. He needs to let it go." Screw you. I'm so happy there's no school tomorrow. I need a break. So bad. SOoooooooooooooooooo bad.Have you ever felt like you were rejected? Not because someone actually rejected you. It's like......a small anxiety attack. Just.....for no reason you felt as if you were rejected. For NO REASON AT ALL. DAAAAAAAAAANGIT. This sucks. I hate feeling like this.

Today was a strange day...kind of a weird one too. Well, school started on Wednesday...it was alright I guess. Actually that's a lie, it really sucks. It never quits.

Well, after getting some homework on our 3rd day of school, I went to band practice. It was...okay I'll tell you about it.

To start out, my amp doesn't work too well. Some people at camp last summer broke it on accident when they were doing a  play. It worked just fine for the next year or so, until like...a couple weeks ago. I've been frustrated at it since.

So today, we were practicing....before we started playing, I prayed that my amp would work fine, because we needed to practice. We have a show with the O.C. Supertones in a couple weeks.....

But anyways, my amp was screwing up when we were playing our....like 4th song. And...I totally just snapped. I was so pissed, I kicked my amp, knocked it over, stomped on it, and threw my guitar down. Really hard. Notice I said, really hard.

I went outside to relax. I thought my equipment was fine.....except for my amp, of course. Of course I have a receipt for my amp, I have a 5-year warranty on it. So I could possibly get it fixed. I thought everything was okay, and I just needed to relax.

After a few minutes, I went back inside to just chill with the guys. They handed me my guitar. My heart sank.

I noticed that there was a huge crack on the neck. Yes ma'am, you guessed it, I had broken my guitar. 400$ down the drain. the worst part is, my parents bought it for me. They work so hard to support what I do, and I just wasted it. I don't  have a warranty for it. It's broken. It's gone. Just because of my amp which was already broken, my guitar paid the price.

So yeah. I'm not in a very good mood right now. My mind is just....racing. I don't know what to tell my parents. They are going to be very mad at me. And I just realized that I can't find my receipt for my amp. So I'm pretty much screwed. I have no hope. I have nowhere to turn. My parents are going to murder me. It feels like God is letting this happen to me. I'm not very happy with God right now.

I thought everything was going to be okay, I thought that it wasn't really a big deal, but yup, it really is. 400$ for my guitar. Possibly another 550$ for my amp. I just wasted it all away. I feel so terrible right now. My parents work their arms off, and I just wasted it. Think about how they will feel. They will hurt even more than I do right now. Just because I was angry. Just because I couldn't control my anger.

I don't have any angst. We all have our days. But I tell you, I learned a couple things.

1. You shouldn't blame God for bad things happening, no matter what they are. It's all the devil's fault. As you can tell, I have trouble with that at the moment.

2. Don't be angry. Try your best to just relax, not snap like I did. Because I snapped, I had terrible consequences. And trust me, it's NOT worth it.

I just need hope. And anger management.

I got a keyboard/synthesizer that my teacher at school sold to me. It's really nice, I like to play it. It's fun. I hope to use that in the band that I play in. Keyboards are fun.

Sorry God. AGAIN I have failed you.

Life is hard. I need to do something with more with my life. I'm not good at sports. I'm too young to get a job. I probably won't even get enough money to save up for my parents on their birthday....man I'm such a terrible person.

Okay so........July 6. I left for California. KAYAAM. It was really good, it started out crappy and bland, but got much better as it kept on going. 3 days later, that Saturday, we left for Mexico. We pretty much camped in a desert that had no good showers (unless you wanted to shower with mosquito water), and a wooden box with a ditch under it for a bathroom. it was hilarious. Everyday we went out to a work site and worked on the house for 8 hours a day. we didn't finish it, of course, but we did
quite a bit. Food was good. July 13....left california to come back to my home in Denver, Colorado. (Saw Ina at the airport and rode the same flight with her.) The day after, I went camping for the weekend, which was okay. I don't really want to go into detail about it though...got back from camping today. 
Now i am extremely bored. I miss everyone i met at KAYAAM. I'm trying my best to go to PUC. Yup, this summer is going well. Hopefully later today i can go look for a job....hopefully someone with a kind heart will accept a 14 year old who needs some money.... Have a great week everyone.
